        public java.lang.String[] fill​(int lengthArray)
        Fills an array with object of the String type.

        The strings consist of random alphabetic characters that were taken from the file in the resources. The strings random size from FillingArrayRandomStrings.DEFAULT_MIN_STRING_LENGTH to FillingArrayRandomStrings.DEFAULT_STRING_LENGTH characters.

        The array is created based on the "lengthArray" parameter. The parameter determines the length(size) of the created array.

        public java.lang.String[] fill​(int lengthArray,
                               int lengthString)
        Fills an array with object of the String type.

        The strings consist of random alphabetic characters that were taken from the file in the resources. The strings random size from FillingArrayRandomStrings.DEFAULT_MIN_STRING_LENGTH to FillingArrayRandomStrings.DEFAULT_STRING_LENGTH characters.

        The array is created based on the "lengthArray" parameter. The parameter determines the length(size) of the created array.

        Parameters:

        lengthString - The length of strings.
